Tribal Football AC Milan are ready to sell Manuel Locatelli and Nikola Kalinic this summer. AC Milan’s new owners Elliott Management have made €35m available for new signings – with any extra funds being raised through sales. Locatelli is a target for Sassuolo, with talks scheduled today between the two clubs. AC Milan want €15m for the midfielder. Kalinic, meanwhile, is a top target for Atletico Madrid and is ready to leave after a disappointing season at the San Siro. Sevilla are also keen to tempt the Croatia international to the LaLiga. 